ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The event name for which the data was collected
Visit name
Number of topology defects for left and right hemispheres before topology correction
Maximum dorsal cutoff score in dMRI FM images
Maximum ventral cutoff score in dMRI FM images
Scans available for dMRI B0 unwarp
Notes: 0 = missing scans required for B0 unwarp; 1 = scans available for B0 unwarp

ElementDescription: Phase-encode polarity difference score for dMRI fieldmap
Notes: Negative score indicates fieldmaps with reversed phase-encode polarity; Near-zero scores indicate fieldmaps with same phase-encode polarity

ElementDescription: Root mean square of estimated B0 displacements in phase-encode direction for dMRI fieldmap
Maximum dorsal cutoff score in fMRI FM images
Maximum ventral cutoff score in fMRI FM images
Scans available for fMRI B0 unwarp
Notes: 0 = missing scans required for B0 unwarp; 1 = scans available for B0 unwarp

ElementDescription: Phase-encode polarity difference score for fMRI fieldmap
Notes: Negative score indicates fieldmaps with reversed phase-encode polarity; Near-zero scores indicate fieldmaps with same phase-encode polarity

ElementDescription: Root mean square of estimated B0 displacements in phase-encode direction for fMRI fieldmap
Intrascan temporal signal to noise ratio averaged across runs and averaged within brain mask
Interrscan temporal signal to noise ratio averaged within brain mask
Normalized score indicating displacement and rotation of T2w volume relative to T1w volume
Normalized score indicating stretching of T2w volume relative to T1w volume
Normalized score indicating displacement and rotation of dMRI fieldmap relative to T1w volume
Normalized score indicating stretching of dMRI fieldmap relative to T1w volume
Normalized score indicating displacement and rotation of fMRI fieldmap relative to T1w volume
Normalized score indicating stretching of fMRI fieldmap relative to T1w volume
